&lt;p&gt;Today we type even more than ever during this pandemic. Working from home is a default now.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This AutoHotKey script will add a period after you end a sentence by using two spaces. iPhone style period ending on Windows 10!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- more --&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-ah&#34; data-lang=&#34;ah&#34;&gt;;iPhone style period after space
:*?: ::. `
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;You need to add this to a *.ahk file (maybe in Documents) after installing AutoHotKey which you can get from &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.autohotkey.com/&#34;&gt;https://www.autohotkey.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
